away that minimizes overheads ofremote interaction and idling .While inmany structured
applications thetask ofallocating equal work toprocessors iseasily accomplished, inunstructured
and dynamic applications (such asgame playing and discrete optimization) this task ismore
difficult .Threaded APIs allow the programmer tospecify alarge number ofconcurrent tasks and
support system -level dynamic mapping oftasks toprocessors with aview tominimizing idling
overheads .Byproviding this support atthesystem level, threaded APIs ridtheprogrammer ofthe
burden ofexplicit scheduling and load balancing .
•Ease ofprogramming and widespread use.
–Due totheaforementioned advantages, threaded programs aresignificantly easier towrite than
corresponding programs using message passing APIs .Achieving identical levels ofperformance for
the two programs may require additional effort, however .With widespread acceptance ofthe
POSIX thread API, development tools forPOSIX threads aremore widely available and stable .These
